{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Give \u00a3500 of credits to full-time workers to spend in UK independent businesses",
        "additional_details": "People are working full time yet still struggling to pay bills, trapped in low-paid or unstable jobs, or avoiding fulltime work because it doesn\u2019t pay. The economy and the high street is dying, its easy to buy cheap, low-quality or imported produce from big corps. \u00a3500 into workers pockets to spend in UK independent shops where 60% of goods are produced in the UK would boost jobs, support SME's which are the backbone of the economy, improve diet & lifestyle, & encourage businesses to reshore.",
        "background": "Introduce a scheme that gives \u00a3500 to adults working at least 35hrs per week to spend in independent businesses that sell goods not services, excluding tobacco, alcohol and fast food. Thus creating entry-level jobs, boosting local spending, strengthening high streets, keeping money in circulation.",
